<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity futures and options trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Dealers reported a dull and uneventful expiry of the June index options and
index futures, leaving traders to focus on weaker gilts and early losses on
Wall Street, writes Joel Kibazo.
The mid-morning expiry in futures saw the June contract finish trading at
3,038 on volume of 6,083 lots. September, the new market leader after June's
close, finished at 3,013, at a 5 point discount to cash, on volume of 16,341
lots.
Turnover in traded options was 36,942 contracts, of which 19,758 was dealt
in the FT-SE 100 option.
