<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Black pepper prices continued firm in Europe while white pepper's
stabilised, reports Man Producten. The black ASTA grades were steady in most
origins, like Indonesia, India, Malaysia and Brazil. Prices for the faq
grades again went up considerabely. Malaysia and Vietnam were out of the
market as local prices were very high. In the US spot black pepper remained
at 86 cents a pound; June-July shipment was at 85 cents. In Europe the faq
grade increased further to Dollars 1,700 a tonne. Grade 1 was traded at
Dollars 1,775 a tonne, spot Rotterdam. White pepper prices improved slightly
in Europe. Muntok faq spot Rotterdam was at Dollars 2,950 a tonne, with
June/July shipment at Dollars 2,875, cif. Markets for other spices were
generally unchanged.
