FT  18 JUN 94 / Letters to the Editor: The train running early is late
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Dr JOHN GODFREY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Does the permanent way have a recurring tendency to temporary
derailment?
As evidence, may I cite something that we passengers were told by
loudspeaker on a long stationary tube train recently?
'We regret to announce
You will be running late,
Due to an unusual delay.
Thank you for travelling
On the Central Line.
The present delay
Was caused because
We have been running early.'
John Godfrey,
41 Lawford Road,
London,
NW5 2LG
