<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 94 / International Company News: Peru sells 49% stake in cement
producer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SALLY BOWEN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LIMA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Peruvian government has sold its minority holding in Cementos Lima, the
cement producer. The auction, held in Lima, was Peru's first
over-the-counter primary offering for a privatisation.
Proceeds from the sale of the 49 per cent holding - comprising some 309,000
voting shares - topped Dollars 103m. The 39 per cent auctioned fetched
Dollars 82m while existing shareholders paid Dollars 21m for another 10 per
cent, the equivalent of the final price.
Lead managers for the sale were Bankers Trust of New York.
Thirteen stockbrokers presented bids which finally secured 41 per cent of
the allocation at the clearing price of Dollars 266 a share.
</TEXT>
