<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 94 / International Company News: Hermes forms alliance
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HILARY BARNES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COPENHAGEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hermes, the German credit insurance group, and Dansk Kaution, the Danish
credit risk insurance company, have agreed a strategic alliance.
The German company would pay about DKr105m (Dollars 16.1m) for a 20 per cent
stake in the Danish company, while Dansk Kaution would acquire a 30 per cent
holding in Hermes's Swedish credit insurance company for DKr12m, Dansk
Kaution said yesterday.
Dansk Kaution's articles of association, which prevent any one shareholder
from owning more than 12 per cent of the company, must be changed before the
alliance can come into force.
