<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 94 / FT Guide to World Cup Football (22): Group D - Greece
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER BERLIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Greece, helped by the withdrawal of Yugoslavia, one of the seeds in their
group, galloped through their qualifying matches. Apart from Germany, the
holders, they were the first European country to qualify for the US.
It will be Greece's first finals appearance. Even so, for many of their
players, it was too late: these are the ancient Greeks. In recent friendlies
they have used up to seven over-30s and three over-35s. Captain Tasos
Mitropoulos is 37, goalkeeper Antonis Minou is 36.
The team's recent form has been poor. It lost 3-0 at home to Colombia, was
booed in a 0-0 draw at home against Bolivia, and lost 5-0 at Wembley against
England. In that game the Greeks passed prettily and skilfully but were
carved open by the English. It seems that, on their debut, the Greeks will
be happy to adorn the World Cup. Even the one win that could carry Greece
into the second round could be beyond them.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GRZ  Greece, EC.
