<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Rea Brothers shares fall on bonds warning
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON DAVIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Rea Brothers, the private banking group, yesterday fell 13p to 62p
after the company issued a profits warning, indicating substantial interim
losses against the value of its Pounds 7m fixed interest securities
portfolio.
The company said that its core businesses had recorded profits 'in excess of
Pounds 1m'. But given the sharp decline in the price of medium-term bonds,
this would be reduced by up to Pounds 700,000 of unrealised losses from its
bond portfolio.
Kleinwort Benson, the house broker, has reduced its forecast for the year
from Pounds 2.2m to Pounds 1.5m, and interim profits of less than Pounds
500,000 (Pounds 802,000) are expected.
Nevertheless, Rea maintains a strong balance sheet, with shareholders funds
of Pounds 23m, and its banking, corporate finance and fund management
businesses continue to show earnings growth.
</TEXT>
